    "methodology": "Unemployment rates from Labour Force Survey (LFS) via NOMIS API. Quarterly data, 3-month rolling average. Youth unemployment uses ILO definition: 18-24 year olds without work, available and seeking work. Economic inactivity covers those not in employment and not seeking work, including long-term sick, carers, students and early retirees. Small sample sizes mean regional youth figures have wide confidence intervals.",
